The Senate Intelligence Committee said on 19 May that Comey would testify before the panel publicly at some point after the 29 May Memorial Day holiday. WASHINGTON Former FBI Director James Comey plans to confirm reports that President Trump pressured him to drop an investigation into former national security adviser Michael Flynn's ties to Russia in congressional testimony, CNN said on Wednesday, citing an unidentified source close to the issue.The Senate Intelligence Committee said on 19 May that Comey, who was fired by Trump earlier in the month, would testify before the panel publicly at some point after the 29 May Memorial Day holiday. CNN said the testimony could come as early as next week.